'''''Star Wars Insider'' 93''' was the first issue of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine to be published by [[Titan Magazines]], published on [[April 24]], [[2007]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"Editor's Welcome" {{C|by [[Brian J. Robb]]}}
*"[[Com-Scan]]"
*"[[Best of StarWars.com]]" &mdash; Koto's Three Dimensional Duel {{C|by [[Pete Vilmur]] & [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*"[[Jawa's Corner]]"
**Books &mdash; [[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice|Sacrificial Writes]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
**Comics &mdash; [[Star Wars: Rebellion: The Ahakista Gambit|Suicide Mission]] {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
**Toys &mdash; Toy Invasion! {{C|by [[Frank Parisi]]}}
**[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] &mdash; Luke's a Back Seat Driver {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
**[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Finding a ''Star Wars'' Story on Tape for Alyssa's Dad {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
**[[International Collecting]] &mdash; Turkey {{C|by [[Gus Lopez]]}}
**[[Set Piece]]" &mdash; Imperial TIE Fighter {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
**[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 24 {{C|by [[Mary Franklin]]}}
**[[Indy Vault]] #1 {{C|by J. W. Rinzler}}
**[[Comlink (department)|Comlink Letters]]

===Features===
*"[[May The Facts Be With You: Part One]]: #1-50" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Discover the first 50 things out of 100 you didn't know about {{Film|IV}}!</small>
*"[[Unleash Your Inner Sith! Inside The Force Unleashed|Unleash Your Inner Sith! Inside ''The Force Unleashed'']]" {{C|by [[Frank Parisi]]}}
*:<small>Be seduced by the power of the Sith as the hotly anticipated new video game ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]'' offers players the chance to become Darth Vader's secret apprentice. ''Star Wars Insider'' takes a sneak peek at what lies ahead as you embark on what could be your journey to the dark side.</small>
*"[[Pirates of the Boards]]: Part Three" by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler|J. W. Rinzler]]
*:<small>Another treasure trove of lost storyboards from the original ''Star Wars'' movie throws new light on the development of the film.</small>
*"[[Part of the Language]]" {{C|by [[Karen Traviss]]}}
*:<small>Thirty years on, ''Star Wars'' has left its mark on the way we talk and think. ''Star Wars'' novelist Karen Traviss investigates.</small>

